ECPDPostCreateAsync
	•	Runs when: An ECPD record is created
	•	Stage: Post-Operation (Async)
	•	What it does:
	•	Creates a team member record for the ECPD owner (only for interactive users)
	•	For related ECPD Contact records:
	•	Builds a unique contact identifier
	•	Syncs Account–Contact relationships based on the ECPD profile’s account

⸻

2. ECPDPostUpdateAsync
	•	Runs when: An ECPD record is updated
	•	Stage: Post-Operation (Async)
	•	What it does:
	•	Detects account changes by comparing old and new values
	•	Expires old ECPD usage records in bulk when needed
	•	If the ECPD account changes:
	•	Updates relationships for all related contacts (N:N and custom junctions)
	•	Removes old links and creates new ones
	•	For ECPD Contact records:
	•	Rebuilds identifiers if relevant fields changed
	•	Keeps Account–Contact relationships in sync
	•	If vz_clsid changes:
	•	Updates related Opportunity parent accounts
	•	Flags records for user review where required
